   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE EXPERIENCE OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>GOD S ORGANIC SALVATION EQUALING</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>REIGNING IN CHRIST S LIFE MESSAGE FIVE REIGNING IN LIFE 2 IN ESTABLISHING NOT OUR OWN RIGHTEOUSNESS BUT GOD S RIGHTEOUSNESS AND TAKING CHRIST AS</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>GOD S RIGHTEOUSNESS; IN PRESENTING OUR BODIES</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>TO LIVE THE BODY LIFE AND RECEIVING</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>THE BELIEVERS TO LIVE THE CHURCH LIFE OUTLINE In establishing not our own righteousness but God s righteousness Rom 9:14 10:4: Being exceptionally strengthened in establishing not our own righteousness but God s righteousness in our reigning with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Being exceptionally radiant in establishing not our own righteousness but God s righteousness in our reigning with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In taking Christ as God s righteousness Rom 10:4; Phil 3:9; 1 Cor 1:30: Being exceptionally extolling in taking Christ as God s righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Being exceptionally successful in taking Christ as God s righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Notes:</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God s righteousness is the way of His acts Psa 103:6-7 ; it is revealed in the gospel of God as its foundation, solid and steadfast as the foundation of God s throne Rom 1:17; Psa 89:14.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The lawkeepers attempt to keep the law for the building up of their own righteousness Rom 9:31 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>But out of the works of the law no flesh shall be justified before Him God 3:20 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Christ is the end of the law by fulfilling all the requirements of God s righteousness, holiness, and glory, and is made the righteousness from God to the believers Rom 10:4; 1 Cor 1:30; Phil 3:9 in two aspects objectively and subjectively.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In presenting our bodies to live the Body life Rom 12 13: Being exceptionally practical in presenting our bodies to live the Body life.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Being exceptionally abounding in presenting our bodies to live the Body life: To present our bodies 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To be renewed in our mind vv.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>2-3.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To exercise our gifts vv.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>4-8.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To live a life of the highest virtues vv.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>9-21.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>To be subject to authorities 13:1-7.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To practice love vv.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>8-10.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>To live a watchful life vv.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>11-14.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>In receiving the believers to live the church life Rom 14:1 15:13: Being exceptionally general in receiving the believers to live the church life: According to God s receiving 14:1-23.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>According to Christ s receiving 15:1-13.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Being exceptionally smooth and orderly in receiving the believers to live the church life: Living the kingdom life not for eating and drinking, but for righteousness, peace, and joy in the Holy Spirit, pursuing peace and the building up of one another 14:17-19.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Being of the same mind toward one another according to Christ Jesus so that with one accord we may glorify God 15:5-7.</S>
   </TEXT>
